Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_wire_load_selection_group(25.10)      set_wire_load_selection_group(25.10)

Name
       set_wire_load_selection_group - Overrides the wire load selection table
       in the specified library

Syntax
        set_wire_load_selection_group

       [-help]

       <wireload_selection_group_name>

       [<list_of_instances>]

       [-library <library_name>]

       [-max]

       [-min]

       Overrides the wire load selection table in the specified library.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each set_wire_load_selection_group parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man

              set_wire_load_selection_group

       -library <library_name>
              Specifies the name of the technology library to search  for  the
              wire load selection table.

              When  this parameter is not specified, the software searches all
              the libraries.

       <list_of_instances>
              Specifies the list of instances.

       -max   Controls the choice of a wire load selection table only for  the
              PVT max corner.

              Default:  Selects  the  table for all PVT corners if neither the
              -min nor the -max parameter is specified.

       -min   Controls the choice of a wire load selection table only for  the
              minimum PVT corner.

              Default:  Selects  the  table for all PVT corners if neither the
              -min nor the -max parameter is specified.

       <wireload_selection_group_name>
              Specifies the name of the wire load selection group.

Examples
              * The following command selects TLM as the selection table  used
                by the library:

                set_wire_load_selection_group TLM

              * The  following  command  selects ASPEC1 as the selection table
                used by the sm333s library; only the minimum PVT corner is af-
                fected:

                set_wire_load_selection_group -min -library sm333s ASPEC1

